cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses the virtualization of base station functionalities and the management of low-cost wireless access points, which are topics related to network infrastructure and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses fronthaul compression, baseband processing, medium access control, resource allocation, and system-level considerations, which are topics related to information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) the second likely sub-category. The paper also touches on topics related to control systems (cs.SY), augmented reality (cs.AR), and multimedia (cs.MM), but to a lesser extent.
